Contributing

We warmly welcome contributions to SignGen Whether it's submitting bug reports, proposing new features, improving documentation, or contributing code, all contributions are greatly appreciated.

How to Contribute
1. Fork the Repository: Start by forking the project repository. This creates your own copy of the project where you can make your changes.
2. Clone the Fork: Clone your forked repository to your local machine, so you can work on the changes.
3. Create a Branch: Create a new branch for your changes. Naming the branch as per the changes you are making is recommended, such as fix-bug-xyz or add-feature-abc.
4. Make Your Changes: Implement your changes, additions, or bug fixes. Make sure to keep your changes concise and focused on a single issue or feature.
5. Test the Changes: Before submitting, ensure that your changes do not break any existing functionality. Add any new tests if necessary.
6. Commit Your Changes: Commit your changes with a clear and descriptive commit message. This message should explain the changes you made and why.
7. Push to Your Fork: Push the changes to your forked repository.
8. Submit a Pull Request (PR): Go to the original repository and submit a pull request. In the PR description, clearly describe the changes and link any related issues.

Best Practices
 - Ensure that your code follows the project's coding standards and style guide.
 - Include documentation with your changes, if applicable.
 - Engage in a respectful and constructive code review process if requested.

Reporting Issues
If you find an issue but are not ready to contribute a fix, you can still help by submitting an issue report. Please include as much detail as possible, such as:

 - A clear title and description of the issue.
 - Steps to reproduce the issue.
 - Expected behavior vs actual behavior.
 - Screenshots or logs if applicable.

Questions or Suggestions?
Feel free to open an issue for any questions or suggestions you might have. We're always looking to improve and value your input!
